// @test regression/tuple-return-series-condition
// @description A tuple destructured from a UDF whose return is a tuple of series gets its members series-typed, so a later `if c > o` is recognized as series-conditional and the history-dependent `ta.stdev` call inside it warns (CW10004). Without the inference, `o`/`c` are untyped, the condition reads non-series, and we miss TV's warning. Probed 2026-06-25, see INV117. (The standard idiom is `[stOpen, stHigh, stLow, stClose] = getStandardOHLC()`.)
// @expects parse: success
// @expects warning: line=8, message="The function 'ta.stdev' should be called on each calculation"
// @expects warnings: 1

//@version=6
indicator("tuple-return-series-condition")
getOHLC() =>
    [open, high, low, close]
[o, h, l, c] = getOHLC()
v = 0.0
if c > o
    v := ta.stdev(close, 5)
plot(v)
plot(h)
plot(l)
